###                TEMPLATE MODULE 

13o)

if i wanted to install the httpd 

3:01:01

when you use a copy module, it basically mean we are just copying  a file frm my local hostor ansible host and am copying it to a remote host 
so i can use copy module bt it only copy static data, ie the file does nt change at the point of execution
whenever a file doesnt change it means the file doesnt have variables that will be dynamically changed like ansible needs to read a variable when its copying that file
 so copy module is only used on ststic, a file does not change bt if a file has a variable that needs to be read at runtime then copy module will fail thats why we will
use a template module 

#########  so we use template module when you are copying the dynamic files, file that change, meaining a file that has a variable that run 
eg
  am missing a file , (ginger2, right here)
bt if i can just show you an example , if i was installing tomcat


  ******  3:02:52
   this is a playbk to install tomcat


  ---
  - name: Install and configure tomcat
    hosts: web
    gather_facts: false
    vars:                                  ****** i hv some variables that am passing here and am saying mayb this is my REQ version of tomcat, can someone find the latest
      req_java: java-1.8.0-openjdk                    
      set_java: jre-1.8.0-openjdk
      req_tomcat_ver: 9.0.83
      tomcat_url: http://mirrors.estointernet.in/apache/tomcat/tomcat-{{req_tomcat_ver.split('.')[0]}}/v{{req_tomcat_ver}}/bin/apache-tomcat-{{req_tomcat_ver}}.tar.gz
      tomcat_port: 8095                            ******* am also passing the port as a var, in prod we always want to use a custom port, so i can pass 8090 0r 8095
    become: yes                                         bt for me to customize is bc am passing this tomcat variable 
    tasks:
      - name: Updating repos
        yum:
          name: "*"
          state: latest
      - name: Installing required java
        yum:
          name: "{{req_java}}"
          state: present
      - name: Setting default java
        alternatives:
          name: java
          link: /usr/bin/java
          path: /usr/lib/jvm/{{set_java}}/bin/java
      - name: Downloading required tomcat
        get_url:
          url: "{{tomcat_url}}"
          dest: /usr/local 
      - name: Extracting downloaded tomcat
        unarchive:                                                                 3:13:27******* its unarchaving it 
          src: "/usr/local/apache-tomcat-{{req_tomcat_ver}}.tar.gz"          ****** from here
          dest: /usr/local                                                       ******** the detsination
          remote_src: yes                                                     ********* so evrtin the source to detsination is happening inside your remote server
      - name: Renaming tomcat home                                                 ***** renmaing the tomcat using the move command to usr/local
        command: mv /usr/local/apache-tomcat-{{req_tomcat_ver}} /usr/local/latest
      - name: Replacing default port with required port                                            *** we are replacing that template then we are starting tomcat 
        template:
          src: server.xml.j2                                    **** i hv to replace this file 
          dest: /usr/local/latest/conf/server.xml                       **** replace it in the cong dir 
      - name: Starting tomcat
        shell:  nohup /usr/local/latest/bin/startup.sh &



  ********************************

             <Connector port="{{tomcat_port}}" protocol="HTTP/1.1"
               connectionTimeout="20000"
               redirectPort="8443" />

   
