*********** where is the tomcat port configured inside of my tomcat??
so i need to find out where this tomcat is actually configured so inside of my tomcat i hv  what we call the server.xml  
so i can copy a server.xml frm a tomacat
when i look at the particular server.xml
when i open the file and scroll up thers what is called a connector port , this is your tomcat port where that runs
but by default here it will just hv 8080  but i want to dynamically change the port so am passing this tomcat port as a variable 
so hv copied this sever.xml file and bc its a variable its a ginger2, this is ginger2 templating bc this one becomes as a template
so your file needs to end with a .j2 which is the extention for ginger templating so bc am using this server.xml as a template
********
its a template bc i hv a variable that will only be read when the playbk is running so this becomes a dynamic file, so i cant use a copy module to copy this bc a copy
module will nt be able to interpolate the value , 
copy module will just copy the file as it is and just transfer it bt bc i want to dynamically read values as the file is been copied then ill use a template module 
(install_tomcat.yml)

***** so for this template module am installing tomcat bt i hv to replace, i hv to get this file server.xml and i need to replace it in the confg dir cos thats wher that
server.xml is                ******* i bliv the 2 files is the server.xml & the dynamic file (ginger) we now hv inside the server.xml file , the giner is an xtension file
so what am doing is that am just replacing the file ,i hv an exact copy of the file but am using a template to go and replace those 2files bc when it replaces it, it wil 
replace it with this file( install_tomcat.yml) that has a diff port bc am pasing my tomcat port as a variable that is now goin to be passed inside of the server.xml file 
and now that port insid eof the instance will be 8095,instaed of 8090 ,so am using this template module to be able to install  tomcat so everything has been passed as 
variables so am able to mange variables in one location just by declaring vars: there ,then once that is declared
this is the tomcat url that hv also passed as a varaible, bc in the download part (using get url,) am just calling the tomcat url as a variable and its replacing the REQ 
tomact version 


