  i wnat to install pip, tree, vim,
if i hv more packages, it just means ill just keep writing but this becomes a very long playbk
so instaed of writing all these long lines of code, i can use a loop, 
 
        ********    loops.yml
            in this loop am just saying
   ---
  - hosts: web
    gather_facts: false
    become: yes
    tasks:
    - apt:                     ******* am using apt
       name: "{{item}}"              ******** and the name is , am passing here as a variable called item (i guess the callibres)
       state: present                   ****** present 
      loop:                                ******* then once i pass the loop, it is goin to loop tru these items, these will be called items 
          - git                                        and for evry item, it will be installed.
          - wget
          - pip3
          - tree
          - vim

****** so i can use a loop and just use list my items like this bt the name of the thing swe wnt to install is called an item, so it will be looping , eg
the first time the item is git it will be replaced in the calibres, it continues until all are installed

